BloodHound Code of Conduct
1. Purpose

BloodHound aims to provide a tool for analyzing and improving Active Directory security. This Code of Conduct outlines our expectations for participants within the BloodHound community to ensure a positive, constructive, and respectful environment.
2. Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to all community spaces, including but not limited to GitHub repositories, forums, chat channels, and social media. It also applies to interactions in both public and private spaces when representing the BloodHound project.
3. Expected Behavior

    Be Respectful: Show respect to all community members, regardless of their background, experience level, or perspective.
    Be Considerate: Consider the impact of your words and actions on others. Be mindful that your contributions affect others and contribute positively.
    Be Collaborative: Work together with other members of the community. Share knowledge and resources generously.
    Use Inclusive Language: Avoid discriminatory language and practices. Promote inclusivity in all interactions and communications.
    Follow Community Guidelines: Adhere to the rules and guidelines established for community spaces. Respect the decisions of moderators and administrators.

4. Unacceptable Behavior

    Harassment: This includes offensive comments, personal attacks, threats, or any form of discrimination.
    Trolling or Insulting: Avoid inflammatory remarks, trolling, or insulting behavior.
    Disrespecting Boundaries: Respect the privacy and personal boundaries of others.
    Spamming: Refrain from spamming community channels with irrelevant or unsolicited content.
    Plagiarism: Do not use others’ work without appropriate credit or permission.

5. Reporting and Enforcement

    Reporting: If you witness or experience behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, report it to the BloodHound community moderators or administrators.
    Enforcement: Community moderators and administrators will review and investigate all reported incidents. They are empowered to take appropriate action, including warnings, temporary bans, or permanent expulsion from the community.

6. Acknowledgment

By participating in the BloodHound community, you acknowledge and agree to adhere to this Code of Conduct. The community’s strength lies in its members' commitment to a respectful and collaborative environment.
7. Updates to the Code of Conduct

This Code of Conduct may be updated periodically to reflect the evolving needs and values of the BloodHound community. Community members will be notified of any significant changes.
Contact Information

For any questions or concerns regarding this Code of Conduct, please contact me.

